=====Usage notes=====
* This word is phonologically an [[enclitic]], similar to [[particle]]s. It is classified as {{m|ja|助動詞|tr=jodōshi||auxiliary verb}} in traditional Japanese grammar.
* This verb only applies to nouns and ''na''-adjectives. An ''i''-adjective or verb alone suffices to end a sentence or clause. For example, {{m|ja|美しい|tr=utsukushii}} could mean "it's beautiful" as a complete grammatical sentence, analogous to {{m|ja|[[綺麗]]'''だ'''|tr=kirei da|t=It's pretty}}.
** The polite form {{m|ja|です|tr=desu}} can be applied to ''i''-adjectives, while {{m|ja|だろう|tr=darō}} / {{m|ja|でしょう|tr=deshō}} and {{m|ja|なら|tr=nara}} can be applied to both ''i''-adjectives and verbs.
* だ cannot be used to introduce a relative clause ending in a ''na''-adjective or noun – {{m|ja|[[学生]]'''だ'''[[アリス]]}} doesn't work, nor does {{m|ja|です}} here.  However, some of the conjugations of だ can: {{m|ja|[[学生]][[である]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who is a student), {{m|ja|[[学生]][[だった]]/[[であった]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who was a student), {{m|ja|[[学生]][[ではない]]/[[じゃない]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who is not a student), {{m|ja|[[学生]][[ではなかった]]/[[じゃなかった]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who was not a student).

